              Brandon Harwood is a designer with a multidisciplinary background spanning UX & visual design, social sciences, emergent technology, creative facilitation, filmmaking, business strategy, and art. He investigates the social and psychological models that drive collective ideation, culture, imagination, and creativity to explore the interchange between these subjects and emerging futures in design and technology. Through speculative design, research, and storytelling, he builds artifacts, interfaces, and ecosystems that address complex challenges in tools for creativity, and collaboration, enabling evolutions in human connection and insight while examining broader implications of these mutations on individuals, systems, and social structures.
            </p>
            <p>
              Brandon’s projects emphasize fluid and adaptive collaboration, where ideas evolve within shared ecosystems of thought. These might look like digital platforms, interactive prototypes, facilitation strategies, design frameworks, games, or dynamic physical experiences. By prioritizing context, connection, and the needs exposed within human expression, he seeks to craft environments where creativity emerges not through rigid structures, but through organic networks of interconnected insights, opinions, and experiences. 
            </p>
            <p>
